```json
{
  "application": "PBS",
  "details": {
    "job_name": "hrrr_gempak_17",
    "walltime": "01:30:00",
    "queue": "dev",
    "account": "HRRR-DEV",
    "nodes": "1",
    "cpus": "1",
    "environment": {
      "OMP_NUM_THREADS": "1",
      "envir": "canned",
      "RUN_ENVIR": "prod",
      "cyc": "17",
      "job": "hrrr_gempak_17",
      "group_name": "meso",
      "dom": "conus",
      "NWROOT": "/lfs/h2/emc/lam/noscrub/Benjamin.Blake/nwprod",
      "DATAROOT": "/lfs/h2/emc/ptmp/Benjamin.Blake"
    },
    "modules": [
      "envvar",
      "PrgEnv-intel",
      "craype",
      "intel",
      "cray-mpich",
      "hdf5",
      "netcdf",
      "pnetcdf",
      "prod_util",
      "util_shared",
      "cray-pals",
      "gempak"
    ],
    "executable": "/lfs/h2/emc/lam/noscrub/Benjamin.Blake/nwprod/hrrr.${hrrr_ver}/jobs/JHRRR_GEMPAK"
  }
}
```

This script uses the **PBS** (Portable Batch System) to run a job on a high-performance computing (HPC) system. The script specifies various parameters for the job, including the job name, walltime, queue, account, number of nodes, number of CPUs, and the modules needed to run the job. The environment variables set within the script provide configuration parameters for the job, and the script eventually calls the executable "JHRRR_GEMPAK" from the HRRR model's job directory. The output format provided is in raw JSON, including the application and its details.
